You are building Phase 16 of the Yuni dating app. Read CLAUDE.md for full project context. Phases 0-15 are complete.

Build the admin dashboard as a Next.js web application.

## 1. dashboard/src/lib/api.ts

Create a fetch wrapper for the admin API:
- Base URL: `http://localhost:8000` (configurable via env)
- `fetchApi(path, options?)` — adds Authorization header from stored token, handles JSON parsing, throws on non-2xx
- `login(email, password)` — POST /api/auth/login, store token in localStorage
- `getUsers(params?)` — GET /api/admin/users
- `getUserDetail(id)` — GET /api/admin/users/{id}
- `updateUser(id, data)` — PATCH /api/admin/users/{id}
- `getPendingRequests()` — GET /api/admin/date-requests/pending
- `createManualGroup(data)` — POST /api/admin/matching/manual
- `runBatchMatching()` — POST /api/admin/matching/run-batch
- `getReports(params?)` — GET /api/admin/reports
- `updateReport(id, data)` — PATCH /api/admin/reports/{id}
- `getAnalytics()` — GET /api/admin/analytics
- `triggerNoshowCheck()` — POST /api/admin/noshow-check
- `seedDatabase()` — POST /api/admin/seed

## 2. Dashboard Layout

### dashboard/src/app/layout.tsx
- Root layout with Tailwind CSS
- Inter font from next/font
- Dark theme (dark background, light text) — modern admin look

### dashboard/src/components/Sidebar.tsx (client component)
- Fixed sidebar with navigation links:
  - Dashboard (overview)
  - Matching (manual matching)
  - Users
  - Reports
  - Analytics
- Yuni logo/text at top
- Active link highlighting
- Logout button at bottom

### dashboard/src/components/AdminAuthGuard.tsx (client component)
- Check for auth token in localStorage
- If no token: show login form
- If token: render children
- Include login form: email + password inputs + submit button

## 3. Pages

### dashboard/src/app/page.tsx
Redirect to /dashboard

### dashboard/src/app/dashboard/page.tsx — Overview
- Stats cards in a grid: Total Users, Active Users, Total Groups, Total Matches, Pending Reports, Avg Rating
- Fetch from /api/admin/analytics
- Each card: icon, label, value, trend color

### dashboard/src/app/matching/page.tsx — Manual Matching
This is the most important page for MVP.

- **Pending Requests Table**: show all pending date requests with columns: User Name, Gender, Age, Activity, Group Size, Availability, Pre-grouped With, Created At
- **Manual Match Form**:
  - Select users from the pending requests (checkboxes)
  - Show selected users count and gender split (e.g., "Selected: 2M, 2F")
  - Activity dropdown, date picker, time input
  - "Create Group" button — calls createManualGroup
  - Validation: must be 4 or 6, equal gender split
- **"Run Batch Matching" button** — triggers automatic matching, shows results
- Color-code rows by activity for easy visual grouping

### dashboard/src/app/users/page.tsx — User List
- Search bar (searches name/email)
- Filter: gender, suspended status
- Table: Name, Email, Gender, Age, Verified, Suspended, No-Shows, Groups, Matches, Joined
- Click row → navigate to user detail
- Pagination

### dashboard/src/app/users/[id]/page.tsx — User Detail
- User profile card: photo, name, email, age, gender, program, bio, interests
- Status badges: verified, selfie verified, suspended, admin
- Actions: Suspend/Unsuspend button, Make Admin button
- Tabs or sections:
  - Groups: list of groups this user has been in
  - Matches: list of mutual matches
  - Reports Filed: reports this user has made
  - Reports Received: reports against this user
  - Date Requests: current and past requests

### dashboard/src/app/reports/page.tsx — Report Queue
- Filter by status (pending, reviewed, resolved, dismissed)
- Table: Reporter, Reported User, Category, Group, Date, Status
- Click to expand: show description, admin notes
- Action buttons: Mark as Reviewed, Resolve, Dismiss
- Admin notes text input on each report

### dashboard/src/app/analytics/page.tsx — Analytics
- Summary stats (same as dashboard overview but more detailed)
- For MVP, just display the numbers in a clean layout — no charts library needed
- Sections: User Stats, Matching Stats, Feedback Stats, Safety Stats
- "Seed Database" button (dev only) — calls seedDatabase endpoint
- "Check No-Shows" button — calls triggerNoshowCheck

## 4. Tests

### dashboard/__tests__/api.test.ts
- Mock fetch. Verify getUsers calls GET /api/admin/users
- Verify createManualGroup sends correct payload

### dashboard/__tests__/matching.test.tsx
- Renders pending requests table heading
- Renders "Create Group" button

IMPORTANT:
- Use Tailwind CSS for ALL styling
- Use "use client" directive only on components that need interactivity (forms, buttons, state)
- The matching page is the most critical page — admins will live here for MVP
- Make the UI clean and functional, not flashy
- TypeScript must compile: `npx tsc --noEmit` and `npm run build` must both pass
- Use standard HTML table elements styled with Tailwind, not a table library
